A critical inflection point was the EPP Pivot of March 31, 2023. Originally, Phase 1B and Phase 2 were planned to go through IPP (PayPal's Instrument Processing Platform) → Fiserv → Pathward. Post-pivot, Braintree moved to integrate directly with Fiserv, cutting out IPP as an intermediary. This had significant implications for the disputes team: instead of receiving dispute data indirectly through IPP's existing file-based mechanism, Braintree would now query Fiserv's Snowflake instance directly. The Phase 1B/2 disputes confluence document was copied from the Phase 4 doc on 5/24/2023 to reflect this new reality.
4.2 Dual Pipeline Reality (Transition Period)
A particularly complex aspect of the transition period was that merchants would have disputes on BOTH the Wells pipeline and the new Fiserv/Pathward pipeline simultaneously. Braintree had to continue processing existing Wells disputes with no interruption while also handling new Fiserv disputes for migrated merchants. This dual-pipeline operation required careful strategy engine design to avoid collisions, duplicate dispute creation, and incorrect financial events.
