9.5 DFM SQL Query (Fiserv's Internal View)
The team also obtained and documented the actual SQL query Fiserv uses internally to build the DFM file from their braintree.chargeback_bt_v1 source table. This was valuable for understanding the full data universe available, even if not all fields were consumed by Arbiter. Key fields in the query included: siteid (Location ID), store_nr, mccd (SIC Code), extr_id (External MID), adj_dt (Funded Date), lctn_dba_nm (Location DBA Name), dspn_curr_cd (Chargeback Currency Code), orig_dsput_amt (Chargeback Amount), dsput_rsn_cd (Dispute Reason Code), alt_dsput_id (IDS Case Number), dspn_resp_due_dt (Due Date), acqr_ref_no (ARN), chargeback_cycle, invoice_no, adj_amt (Adjustment Amount), and pre_dsput_flag (Pre-Dispute Flag), among 50+ total fields. The query joined against a metadata_v1 table to decode enumerated values (e.g., cb_status, cb_Reason, cb_authNetwork).
 
