Splitting processor record ingest and handling
The goal of this improvement is to have a ingest job that is responsible for retrieving records (e.g., for Fiserv, querying Snowflake; for Moneris, downloading chargeback activity files), iterating through those records, and creating and persisting processor record objects.
Then, for each record, we either kick off Gateway transaction lookup or queue a separate HandleProcessorRecordJob. At that point, ingest of the record is complete.
The Gateway transaction lookup response would be processed via the ArbiterDisputeMessageService, which would end by queueing a HandleProcessorRecordJob.
The HandleProcessorRecordJob would pass the record to the HandleProcessorRecordService for handling.
As such, ingest, transaction lookup, and handling are separated across workers instead of occurring inline.
