Handling
There would (ideally) be four possible flows for handling a record:
1.	Open record for a new case (i.e., an open retrieval record or an open chargeback-with-no-retrieval record)
o	Ingest process triggers Gateway transaction lookup
o	When transaction lookup completes, ArbiterDisputeMessageService queues a HandleProcessorRecordJob
o	An open Dispute is created
o	The Dispute is evaluated for auto acceptance during creation
o	Notifications (open email and open webhook, or auto accepted webhook) are created appropriately
o	Any financial events are sent to Funding
2.	Open record for an escalated dispute (i.e., an open chargeback-with-retrieval record or a pre-arbitration record)
o	Transaction lookup is not needed; ingest process queues a HandleProcessorRecordJob
o	Otherwise, same as above.
3.	Win or loss record for an existing dispute
o	Transaction lookup is not needed; ingest process queues a HandleProcessorRecordJob
o	The dispute is transitioned to won or lost
o	A won or lost webhook is created
o	Any financial events are sent to Funding
4.	Update record for an existing dispute
o	Same as above, except dispute information is simply updated; the dispute is not transitioned to a terminal state.
We will likely need at least the following strategies: CreateRetrievalStrategy, CreateChargebackStrategy, CreatePreArbitrationStrategy, WinDisputeStrategy, LoseDisputeStrategy and UpdateDisputeStrategy. We should raise a PRE for each record for which no strategies or multiple strategies apply.
There should also be Datadog metrics that provide insight into how long handling takes, etc.
Since Arbiter will be the initial point of ingest, we need to send DisputeFinancialEvents to Funding so that they can move money. This means that logic can be introduced in Funding to waive chargeback fees for pre-disputes on a dispute-by-dispute basis, in contrast to the current approach of blanket-waiving fees for all Visa chargebacks on allowlisted merchant accounts.
We should also continue to receive acknowledgement from Funding that they have received each DisputeFinancialEvent via the FundingDisbursementsConsumer.
